 -- Tim Gardner <tim.gardner@canonical.com>  Fri, 04 Jan 2008 11:39:27 -0700

linux-meta (2.6.24.2.2) hardy; urgency=low

  * Tighten dependencies between metapackages further.  All dependencies
    should now be versioned, either by the metapackage version number or the
    kernel abi version number.  This prevents linux-restricted-modules from
    going MIA during upgrades when things are out of sync

    debian/control.common:
    - linux depends on matching linux-image and linux-restricted-modules
    - linux-image likewise
    - linux-restricted-modules likewise
    - linux-modules-backports-RELEASE_NAME likewise
    debian/control.d/generic:
    - linux-generic likewise
    debian/control:
    - Regenerate

  * Rename ${generic-depends} to ${generic-flavour} as it's just a string
    name, not a full dependency clause

 -- Matt Zimmerman <mdz@ubuntu.com>  Wed, 19 Dec 2007 11:46:56 +0000

linux-meta (2.6.24.2.1) hardy; urgency=low

  * First Hardy release, ABI==2
  * Renamed linux-backports-modules to break the upgrade dependencies
    from Gutsy to Hardy.

 -- Tim Gardner <tim.gardner@canonical.com>  Mon, 17 Dec 2007 07:37:41 -0700

