linux-meta (2.6.22.11.13) gutsy; urgency=low

  * Add linux-image, linux-restricted-modules, and linux-backports-modules
    metapackages, paralleling the existing linux.
  * Add linux-restricted-modules-lpia and linux-backports-modules-lpia. Make
    linux-lpia depend on linux-restricted-modules-lpia too (even though the
    underlying package is currently empty).
  * Make linux-image-lpia depend on
    linux-ubuntu-modules-${kernel-abi-version}-lpia too (LP: #139583).
  * Move everything to Section: metapackages (LP: #114662).
  * Use ${binary:Version} rather than ${Source-Version} to keep lintian
    happy. Update Build-Depends to cope.
  * Update FSF address in copyright file.
  * Use debian/compat rather than DH_COMPAT.
  * Fix Build-Depends to match debhelper compatibility level.

 -- Colin Watson <cjwatson@ubuntu.com>  Tue, 18 Sep 2007 18:17:30 +0100

