linux-meta (2.6.15.7) dapper; urgency=low

  * Kernel ABI bump for linux-source-2.6.15 2.6.15-10
  * Amd64, -k8-smp target gone, should pull -k8 now. All amd64 targets are SMP
    enabled now.
  * Cleanup obsolete -smp targets. No reason to have the lrm, headers and
    image meta packages. Just have the linux-foo-smp target depend on the
    right non-smp versions.
  * Bump DH_COMPAT level to 4

 -- Ben Collins <bcollins@ubuntu.com>  Tue, 27 Dec 2005 11:24:51 -0500

